00:16:52,261 --> 00:16:55,764
Hey. Come back here.
What's the matter with you?

246
00:16:55,932 --> 00:16:58,225
Bye, Mom.
Bye, baby.

247
00:17:00,853 --> 00:17:05,107
WOMAN: Mm-hm. Yes, that's correct.
"Harry gave me a turtle."

248
00:17:05,608 --> 00:17:08,777
Okay. "He drunk that water fast."
Brandie?

249
00:17:08,945 --> 00:17:10,487
BRANDIE:
"He drank that water fast."

250
00:17:10,655 --> 00:17:11,947
TEACHER:
Very good.

251
00:17:12,115 --> 00:17:15,784
"He drank that water fast."

252
00:17:15,952 --> 00:17:18,453
That's the correct answer. Very good.

253
00:17:18,621 --> 00:17:22,124
Okay, Bernice.
All right, class, this is Bernice Pruitt.

254
00:17:22,291 --> 00:17:24,793
Bernice comes to us from Chicago.

255
00:17:26,295 --> 00:17:30,382
You take the desk next to Kristen.
That will be your seat. Kristen?

256
00:17:31,175 --> 00:17:32,843
Go on, honey.

257
00:17:33,010 --> 00:17:37,973
All right, class, let's open up your books
to Page 76, Chapter 3.

258
00:17:38,141 --> 00:17:40,809
Pay attention, because you're gonna have
a quiz on Monday.

259
00:17:40,977 --> 00:17:43,270
She's got pop-eyes.

260
00:17:43,438 --> 00:17:44,730
[CHILDREN GIGGLE]

261
00:17:44,897 --> 00:17:48,483
TEACHER: Bernice, you just follow along
with Kristen, okay?

262
00:17:53,156 --> 00:17:57,325
I didn't do anything.
Why is it always my fault?

263
00:17:57,493 --> 00:18:01,830
I didn't say anything about fault.
I just asked what you did, that's all.

264
00:18:01,998 --> 00:18:03,206
Nothing.

265
00:18:03,374 --> 00:18:05,500
People fall in love,
they fall right back out.

266
00:18:05,668 --> 00:18:06,835
It happens all the time.

267
00:18:07,795 --> 00:18:10,422
You never even told me
you were having trouble with Bill.

268
00:18:12,258 --> 00:18:15,802
Maybe it's because
I didn't want to hear, "l told you so."

269
00:18:17,013 --> 00:18:20,098
Besides,
how could we have trouble?

270
00:18:20,391 --> 00:18:23,727
Prom queen, quarterback,
pride of Smithville.

271
00:18:23,895 --> 00:18:26,563
We practically left town on a float.

272
00:18:28,232 --> 00:18:30,609
Well, maybe you were special.

273
00:18:31,444 --> 00:18:34,196
But then again, maybe you
were just like the rest of us...

274
00:18:34,363 --> 00:18:39,201
...except you were riding around on
flowers made out of toilet paper.

275
00:18:39,368 --> 00:18:40,619
You just never liked Bill.

276
00:18:40,787 --> 00:18:45,040
Oh, l like all of God's creatures.
I just like some of them better stuffed.

277
00:18:45,208 --> 00:18:47,042
And he's one of them.

278
00:18:47,210 --> 00:18:51,004
Why don't you just cut to the part where,
you know, he started fooling around?

279
00:18:51,631 --> 00:18:52,964
[SIGHS]

280
00:18:57,053 --> 00:19:03,725
Well, at cocktail parties, the women
that Bill worked with would never....

281
00:19:04,018 --> 00:19:06,353
They'd never look at me.

282
00:19:07,271 --> 00:19:10,232
Their eyes were always surveying
the room...

283
00:19:10,399 --> 00:19:12,859
...looking for somebody better
to talk to.

284
00:19:15,029 --> 00:19:18,323
I was the beauty queen from Smithville,
worse than ordinary, a joke.

285
00:19:18,491 --> 00:19:19,574
That was it.

286
00:19:19,742 --> 00:19:22,702
No, you were never a joke.

287
00:19:24,580 --> 00:19:26,873
Oh, yeah, I was, Mama.

288
00:19:27,208 --> 00:19:29,626
You could see it in his eyes.
You can't mistake that.

289
00:19:41,389 --> 00:19:46,476
Honey, you know, crying over it
won't make it clean.

290
00:19:47,562 --> 00:19:52,190
Life just goes on and
you gotta move along with it.

291
00:19:52,358 --> 00:19:54,025
Yeah.

292
00:19:58,239 --> 00:19:59,447
Bud.
Weiser.

293
00:20:01,409 --> 00:20:04,452
How's your dinner, Kermit?
Good.

294
00:20:04,620 --> 00:20:07,914
Well, we seem to be
the only ones enjoying it.

295
00:20:08,082 --> 00:20:12,627
Did you ever see two such mopes?
That's a mope and that's a mope.

296
00:20:12,795 --> 00:20:14,170
BIRDEE:
All right, Mama.

297
00:20:14,338 --> 00:20:16,339
RAMONA: No, it isn't all right.
I mean, look at me.

298
00:20:16,507 --> 00:20:22,929
My life has no big meaning or
direction or purpose, and I'm happy.

299
00:20:23,472 --> 00:20:27,601
Look at Kermit here.
You think it's easy being green?

300
00:20:30,229 --> 00:20:31,563
Ribbit.

301
00:20:32,231 --> 00:20:35,859
Oh, l saw that, Bernice.
That smile means there's hope for you.

302
00:20:37,069 --> 00:20:38,111
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

303
00:20:38,279 --> 00:20:39,946
TRAVIS:
I got it!

304
00:20:42,617 --> 00:20:46,661
You expecting someone?
No. I mean, it might be Justin Matisse.

305
00:20:47,455 --> 00:20:50,540
I mean, he said he might drop over
after his day job.

306
00:20:50,708 --> 00:20:52,792
He's helping me fix the porch.

307
00:20:52,960 --> 00:20:55,462
I don't want to see Justin Matisse.
MAN: Hi, Travis.

308
00:20:55,630 --> 00:20:59,424
Why? Because your hair's not fixed?
He's back from California.

309
00:20:59,592 --> 00:21:01,426
So what?
RAMONA: And--

310
00:21:01,594 --> 00:21:04,012
Justin, come on in.
Mama.

311
00:21:10,311 --> 00:21:14,439
Hey, Justin.
Well, well, well.

312
00:21:15,191 --> 00:21:18,944
If it ain't Birdee Calvert.
It's Pruitt. Birdee Pruitt.

313
00:21:19,445 --> 00:21:20,946
Sorry.

314
00:21:21,697 --> 00:21:22,948
It's all right.

315
00:21:24,200 --> 00:21:25,867
Birdee, Birdee, Birdee.

316
00:21:27,370 --> 00:21:29,287
Move on to something else,
Justin.

317
00:21:29,997 --> 00:21:31,373
So l heard you'd come back.

318
00:21:32,625 --> 00:21:34,709
I wonder how.

319
00:21:35,836 --> 00:21:38,380
Oh, this is my daughter, Bernice.

320
00:21:38,547 --> 00:21:40,674
Bernice, Bernice, Bernice.

321
00:21:41,550 --> 00:21:42,884
She's funny.

322
00:21:43,552 --> 00:21:46,638
You smell just delicious, Justin.
JUSTIN: Thanks.

323
00:21:46,806 --> 00:21:47,889
Are you wearing cologne?

324
00:21:48,265 --> 00:21:51,643
Oh, no. That's a little paint thinner.

325
00:21:51,811 --> 00:21:53,728
A little sweat mixed in with it.

326
00:21:54,647 --> 00:21:57,691
RAMONA: Well, it sure does smell good.
Don't it, Birdee?

327
00:21:58,651 --> 00:22:02,320
Why don't you go out on the porch and
I'll have Birdee bring you some iced tea?

328
00:22:02,488 --> 00:22:05,573
That sounds great, Mrs. Calvert.
Thank you. Bye, y'all.

329
00:22:05,741 --> 00:22:07,951
TRAVIS: Bye.
Bye, Bernice, Bernice, Bernice.

330
00:22:08,369 --> 00:22:11,246
Great to see you, Birdee.
You look good.

331
00:22:20,381 --> 00:22:21,506
BERNICE:
Here.

332
00:22:23,259 --> 00:22:27,429
Oh, hey, Bernice. Thank you.

333
00:22:28,180 --> 00:22:30,265
I don't see a glass there for your mother.

334
00:22:30,850 --> 00:22:32,183
She went upstairs.

335
00:22:32,351 --> 00:22:35,270
My daddy usually calls about now
for one of his daily chats...

336
00:22:35,438 --> 00:22:36,730
...and then we all turn in.

337
00:22:36,897 --> 00:22:38,398
I see.

338
00:22:38,941 --> 00:22:41,359
So how do you like it down here
in Smithville?

339
00:22:41,527 --> 00:22:44,738
It wasn't on any maps
until we got to Texas.

340
00:22:46,282 --> 00:22:49,284
Well, see, we like to keep it a secret.

341
00:22:49,452 --> 00:22:51,244
That way,
it doesn't get overrun with people.

342
00:22:51,412 --> 00:22:53,788
It seems to be working.

343
00:22:54,790 --> 00:22:57,959
You know, your mother and l
go way back.

344
00:22:58,127 --> 00:22:59,794
I know you must.

345
00:23:01,630 --> 00:23:06,426
Back home, we had a pet skunk.
Mom called it Justin Matisse.

346
00:23:06,594 --> 00:23:09,137
Do you think that's a coincidence?

347
00:23:09,638 --> 00:23:13,683
All day long, Mom would scream,
"You stink, Justin Matisse."

348
00:23:13,851 --> 00:23:17,228
Finally, she just picked up a club
and killed it.

349
00:23:17,396 --> 00:23:19,105
Well, that's a sad story.

350
00:23:19,982 --> 00:23:22,901
BERNICE: If you like
the skunk, which we didn't.

351
00:23:23,069 --> 00:23:25,779
I think she still has that club
in her purse upstairs.

352
00:23:27,615 --> 00:23:29,866
So l guess that means
she's not coming down, huh?

353
00:23:30,034 --> 00:23:32,452
Not until you leave.

354
00:23:34,121 --> 00:23:36,164
Guess l better go, then.

355
00:23:36,332 --> 00:23:39,417
Hey, thanks for packing up
all my stuff. I appreciate it.

356
00:23:40,169 --> 00:23:42,170
I'll see you around.

357
00:23:42,338 --> 00:23:45,131
That's what's great about a small town.

358
00:23:53,682 --> 00:23:55,683
[DOOR CLOSES]

359
00:23:57,436 --> 00:23:58,853
Birdee!

360
00:23:59,021 --> 00:24:00,855
[TRUCK ENGINE STARTS]

361
00:24:01,023 --> 00:24:04,359
BIRDEE: What, Mama?
Honey, can you give me a hand?

362
00:24:06,320 --> 00:24:08,196
[TRUCK PULLS AWAY]

363
00:24:09,824 --> 00:24:11,825
[DOG BARKING]

364
00:24:18,290 --> 00:24:19,666
[VACUUM WHIRRING]

365
00:24:19,834 --> 00:24:23,128
What? Mama.
Oh. Oh!

366
00:24:24,171 --> 00:24:28,424
Honey, are you still in here?
I had no idea.

367
00:24:28,676 --> 00:24:32,720
It's a beautiful day out.
Just take a look at that.

368
00:24:32,972 --> 00:24:34,055
Go on.

369
00:24:34,223 --> 00:24:37,350
Get out there.
Get the stink blown off you.

370
00:24:37,518 --> 00:24:39,227
I always hated that expression, Mama.

371
00:24:39,395 --> 00:24:42,647
Don't make me use it, then.
I'm gonna turn the shower on for you.

372
00:24:42,815 --> 00:24:46,484
Then I’m going shopping later,
if you want to get out of the house.

373
00:25:05,754 --> 00:25:07,755
[LOUD WHIRRING]

374
00:25:13,429 --> 00:25:17,599
Mama!

375
00:25:18,267 --> 00:25:21,728
Mama, can't this--?
Mama! Mama! Mother!

376
00:25:22,271 --> 00:25:23,605
Justin, hey.

377
00:25:23,772 --> 00:25:25,273
[THE ROLLING STONES' "HONEST l DO"
PLAYS ON RADIO]

378
00:25:25,441 --> 00:25:29,110
What are you doing up here?
I'm building shelves.

379
00:25:29,278 --> 00:25:31,362
You look terrible.

380
00:25:31,906 --> 00:25:33,072
Been drinking, huh?

381
00:25:34,033 --> 00:25:36,451
Why does everybody keep
asking if I've been drinking?

382
00:25:36,619 --> 00:25:41,039
What, is there a coaster stuck
to my butt or something?

383
00:25:41,582 --> 00:25:44,751
How long is this gonna take?
A couple hours.

384
00:25:45,836 --> 00:25:48,963
Why don't you go down
and get dressed? You'll feel better.

385
00:25:49,131 --> 00:25:51,549
You've got to feel depressed
looking like that.

386
00:25:52,509 --> 00:25:55,970
BIRDEE: Do you always say what's
on your mind or is it just my lucky day?

387
00:25:56,138 --> 00:25:58,264
I'm not gonna do you any favors
by lying.

388
00:25:58,432 --> 00:26:02,268
Well, Justin, I don't need your favors,
all right?

389
00:26:02,436 --> 00:26:06,898
I just need something.
Is that an invitation?

390
00:26:07,983 --> 00:26:10,360
Bye.
JUSTIN: Bye.

391
00:26:16,784 --> 00:26:20,787
remember the blue beetle?
It promised us a long and happy life.

392
00:26:20,955 --> 00:26:22,956
[MUSIC PLAYING ON TV]

393
00:26:35,302 --> 00:26:36,469
BERNICE:
Forget it.

394
00:26:40,933 --> 00:26:43,434
TRAVIS: Hansel and Gretel's mother
was a terrible woman.

395
00:26:43,602 --> 00:26:47,522
Why didn't the witch eat her?
I don't think you told the story right.

396
00:26:48,148 --> 00:26:53,027
Honey, your mama is gonna come get you
just as soon as she can, I promise.

397
00:26:53,195 --> 00:26:56,281
Stop picking at that doll's eyes, will you?
That makes me nervous.

398
00:26:56,448 --> 00:26:58,199
BIRDEE:
Bernice!

399
00:26:58,951 --> 00:27:01,411
Bernice! Come here.

400
00:27:01,578 --> 00:27:04,664
What do you think you're doing?
Do you think I am stupid?

401
00:27:04,832 --> 00:27:06,708
I wouldn't find out?
RAMONA: What's the matter?

402
00:27:06,875 --> 00:27:09,043
BIRDEE: What do you think you're doing?
BERNICE: What did l do?

403
00:27:09,211 --> 00:27:11,796
If you have something to say
to me, say it flat out.

404
00:27:11,964 --> 00:27:13,840
Do not say it behind my back.

405
00:27:14,425 --> 00:27:16,342
Do you have something to tell me?
No.

406
00:27:16,510 --> 00:27:18,219
Tell me!
What do you want me to say?

407
00:27:18,387 --> 00:27:21,014
Stop playing innocent!
I know what you told him!

408
00:27:21,223 --> 00:27:23,850
Told who?
Your father. I just got off the phone.

409
00:27:24,018 --> 00:27:27,437
Do you know what he said to me?
"I'm sorry you're taking this so hard.

410
00:27:27,604 --> 00:27:31,107
I'm sorry you can't get out of bed,
but we have a daughter to take care of."

411
00:27:31,275 --> 00:27:32,483
What did you say to him?

412
00:27:32,693 --> 00:27:36,154
Nothing. It wasn't bad.
I just said you were sad. We both are.

413
00:27:36,322 --> 00:27:38,865
That is our business.
That's not his business.

414
00:27:39,033 --> 00:27:40,825
Besides, we're not sad. We're fine.

415
00:27:40,993 --> 00:27:43,745
We are not! You don't care about me,
ask me about school.

416
00:27:43,912 --> 00:27:45,246
You don't make breakfast.

417
00:27:45,414 --> 00:27:47,040
You promised Daddy
you'd take care of me!

418
00:27:47,207 --> 00:27:48,916
I promised Daddy?
Well, you know what?

419
00:27:49,084 --> 00:27:52,253
Daddy promised me the world
and Daddy didn't honor his promise.

420
00:27:52,421 --> 00:27:54,630
I will break every promise
I make to your daddy.

421
00:27:54,798 --> 00:27:57,091
Birdee, stop it. That's enough now.

422
00:27:58,552 --> 00:28:01,554
It is not a crime to tell the truth.
Not in this house.

423
00:28:01,722 --> 00:28:03,097
Don't yell at her.

424
00:28:03,265 --> 00:28:06,559
She's my daughter.
I'll yell at her all l want to.

425
00:28:06,727 --> 00:28:08,478
Will you just take a look at yourself?

426
00:28:08,645 --> 00:28:11,981
Wandering around night and day
in your bathrobe.

427
00:28:12,149 --> 00:28:14,484
You're hiding out. You're scared.

428
00:28:14,693 --> 00:28:17,153
Lord, what happened to you?

429
00:28:18,030 --> 00:28:19,864
You used to be so pleasing.

430
00:28:20,616 --> 00:28:23,826
You know what?
I had to be pleasing, Mama.

431
00:28:23,994 --> 00:28:26,621
With the town joke as a mother,
I had to be pleasing.

432
00:28:26,789 --> 00:28:28,790
When you'd flounce yourself
into school...

433
00:28:30,042 --> 00:28:32,418
...with your roadkill hat
and freshly skinned bag.

434
00:28:32,586 --> 00:28:35,129
Mom, l learned how to be pleasing.

435
00:28:35,297 --> 00:28:38,466
You're pleasing nobody.
You're miserable yourself.

436
00:28:38,634 --> 00:28:42,470
And I've never been unhappy.
So the joke is on you, honey.

437
00:28:43,138 --> 00:28:47,308
BERNICE: Don't yell at her.
Oh, I’m finished, believe me.

438
00:28:47,768 --> 00:28:50,603
Come on, Travis. Come on out here.

439
00:29:11,083 --> 00:29:13,918
I didn't hurt you, did l?

440
00:29:18,173 --> 00:29:21,843
Because I wouldn't hurt you for anything
in the world. You know that, don't you?

441
00:29:26,807 --> 00:29:29,183
It's okay. Night, Travis.

442
00:29:29,560 --> 00:29:31,018
TRAVIS:
Night.

443
00:29:59,131 --> 00:30:01,132
[DISC JOCKEY TALKING ON RADIO]

444
00:30:06,722 --> 00:30:08,222
Excuse me.

445
00:30:09,391 --> 00:30:10,516
[GASPS]

446
00:30:10,684 --> 00:30:13,102
Birdee. Birdee Calvert!

447
00:30:14,188 --> 00:30:16,355
I heard you were back in town.

448
00:30:16,773 --> 00:30:19,567
Hello.
Debbie. Debbie Reissen.

449
00:30:19,735 --> 00:30:21,235
[BARRY MANILOW'S "DAYBREAK"
PLAYS ON RADIO]

450
00:30:21,403 --> 00:30:24,322
Debbie Reissen.
How are you?

451
00:30:24,490 --> 00:30:27,074
How are you?
Did you come here to see Dot?

452
00:30:27,951 --> 00:30:31,078
Dot.
Dot. She runs the whole office now.

453
00:30:31,246 --> 00:30:34,916
Oh, yeah, yeah. I came to see Dot.
She'll be so tickled.

454
00:30:35,083 --> 00:30:36,417
Oh, great.

455
00:30:38,045 --> 00:30:40,922
Dottie, in a million years,
you'll never guess...

456
00:30:41,089 --> 00:30:44,425
...who came all the way from Chicago,
Illinois, to see you.

457
00:30:44,593 --> 00:30:47,261
WOMAN [ON INTERCOM]:
Take me off the intercom, please.

458
00:30:47,429 --> 00:30:51,849
Blinded with fear

459
00:30:52,017 --> 00:30:55,520
She guessed.
Would you like to have a seat?

460
00:30:56,355 --> 00:30:58,814
Great. Thank you.
She'll be right with you.

461
00:30:58,982 --> 00:31:01,317
Ain't no time to grieve

462
00:31:01,485 --> 00:31:03,110
Said it's daybreak

463
00:31:03,278 --> 00:31:05,321
If you'll only believe

464
00:31:05,489 --> 00:31:07,031
I saw you on television.

465
00:31:08,033 --> 00:31:09,075
Really?

466
00:31:09,243 --> 00:31:10,868
I taped it.

467
00:31:11,620 --> 00:31:12,620
Yeah.

468
00:31:12,788 --> 00:31:15,957
Sing it, sing it
Sing it to the world

469
00:31:16,625 --> 00:31:18,292
Sing it, sing it

470
00:31:20,045 --> 00:31:22,088
DOT:
Birdee! Come on in.

471
00:31:22,923 --> 00:31:24,799
No calls, Deborah.

472
00:31:24,967 --> 00:31:26,676
BIRDEE: Hi.
Hi.

473
00:31:33,600 --> 00:31:37,520
DOT: I didn't keep you too long?
Oh, no, it's fine, thank you.

474
00:31:38,438 --> 00:31:42,316
You look beautiful.
Same old Birdee.

475
00:31:43,402 --> 00:31:45,695
Same old Dot.
Heh, heh.

476
00:31:47,155 --> 00:31:48,489
[CHUCKLING]

477
00:31:49,866 --> 00:31:52,660
You have no idea who I am, do you?

478
00:31:54,955 --> 00:31:57,873
No, sorry. I don't.

479
00:31:58,041 --> 00:31:59,500
It's all right.

480
00:32:00,794 --> 00:32:04,964
When I knew you, l was about 5 inches
shorter and about 70 pounds heavier.

481
00:32:06,049 --> 00:32:09,010
We didn't exactly eat
at the same lunch table.

482
00:32:09,177 --> 00:32:10,595
Polka Dot?

483
00:32:10,762 --> 00:32:12,763
[DOT LAUGHING]

484
00:32:13,348 --> 00:32:16,100
Is that right?
Yeah. Ha, ha.

485
00:32:16,268 --> 00:32:19,020
Nobody's called me that
in a long time.

486
00:32:19,187 --> 00:32:22,148
Oh, my God! You look fantastic.

487
00:32:22,524 --> 00:32:23,983
Thank you.
You're welcome.

488
00:32:24,151 --> 00:32:25,192
Have a seat.

489
00:32:26,528 --> 00:32:29,614
Oh, my God. I mean,
it's remarkable.

490
00:32:29,781 --> 00:32:31,991
Was I really that terrible before,
Birdee?

491
00:32:32,159 --> 00:32:36,245
Oh, no, no, no. l just meant that--
Yeah, well, l know what you meant.

492
00:32:36,413 --> 00:32:39,498
People change.
We get better as we get older.

493
00:32:39,666 --> 00:32:40,791
Yeah.

494
00:32:40,959 --> 00:32:43,377
Gosh, you look exactly the same.

495
00:32:45,172 --> 00:32:47,882
Well, no, actually l--
Oh, l know.

496
00:32:48,675 --> 00:32:50,384
I heard about you and Bill.
Yeah.

497
00:32:50,552 --> 00:32:53,429
Yeah, he always was the ladies' man.

498
00:32:54,848 --> 00:32:57,808
You all right?
Oh, I’m fine, I’m fine.

499
00:32:57,976 --> 00:33:01,312
You know, so much of that
is staged for TV.

500
00:33:01,480 --> 00:33:04,023
It's for ratings and....

501
00:33:04,191 --> 00:33:05,358
Yeah.

502
00:33:08,111 --> 00:33:11,072
So you need a job.

503
00:33:11,239 --> 00:33:14,158
What sort of work have you been doing?
Um, housework.

504
00:33:14,910 --> 00:33:17,870
Bill worked and he didn't want--

505
00:33:18,038 --> 00:33:20,665
We have a daughter.
So l took care of her.

506
00:33:21,792 --> 00:33:23,125
Okay.

507
00:33:23,794 --> 00:33:27,380
How fast do you type?
Don't type.

508
00:33:30,300 --> 00:33:33,052
Okay. Computer skills.

509
00:33:34,721 --> 00:33:36,097
Don't compute.

510
00:33:36,264 --> 00:33:37,306
[BOTH LAUGH]

511
00:33:37,474 --> 00:33:39,225
Oh, goodness.

512
00:33:39,601 --> 00:33:43,270
You're gonna have to give me some sort
of idea what you're looking for here...

513
00:33:43,438 --> 00:33:46,273
...because I'm not likely
to find a listing for prom queen.

514
00:33:47,567 --> 00:33:49,110
Well, um...

515
00:33:49,778 --> 00:33:52,780
...l used to take pictures.
I was good at that.

516
00:33:52,948 --> 00:33:56,450
So maybe l could get a job
at the newspaper...

517
00:33:56,618 --> 00:33:59,120
...or Jackson's Portrait Studio.

518
00:33:59,287 --> 00:34:02,456
It's closed down,
and the newspaper is not hiring.

519
00:34:02,624 --> 00:34:04,917
I can tell you that right now.
Oh, okay, okay.

520
00:34:06,378 --> 00:34:07,795
So....

521
00:34:07,963 --> 00:34:13,426
Dot, l would really like a job.

522
00:34:14,636 --> 00:34:17,930
One that I could
like myself for...

523
00:34:18,098 --> 00:34:20,224
...even if it's just
for a little while.

524
00:34:20,809 --> 00:34:22,977
Birdee--
Dot...

525
00:34:25,981 --> 00:34:30,276
...l don't know how l treated you
in high school.

526
00:34:32,362 --> 00:34:36,240
I'm guessing it was pretty bad...

527
00:34:36,408 --> 00:34:41,537
...seeing how you're hell-bent on
putting me in my place right now.

528
00:34:42,080 --> 00:34:43,998
And that's okay.

529
00:34:45,000 --> 00:34:46,751
Just--

530
00:34:47,711 --> 00:34:51,672
Just put me in a job too.

531
00:34:53,675 --> 00:34:56,761
I would really be grateful.

532
00:35:02,809 --> 00:35:04,477
Well....

533
00:35:09,024 --> 00:35:12,276
Shoot some pictures over the weekend.
Okay, great.

534
00:35:12,444 --> 00:35:14,361
I'll look them over.
Great.

535
00:35:14,529 --> 00:35:18,699
I'll do what I can.
Thank you. Thank you.

536
00:35:29,419 --> 00:35:32,880
Enjoy your food, honey.
Thanks.

537
00:35:36,885 --> 00:35:39,220
It's not for sissies,
you know.

538
00:35:39,846 --> 00:35:41,889
Dining alone.

539
00:35:44,100 --> 00:35:46,977
Gotta be made of some
pretty stern stuff to do that.

540
00:35:47,145 --> 00:35:48,687
Really?

541
00:35:49,314 --> 00:35:52,483
See, the trick is
to seem mysterious.

542
00:35:54,027 --> 00:35:56,403
Like the choice is yours.

543
00:36:02,494 --> 00:36:04,286
Impressive.

544
00:36:05,121 --> 00:36:07,748
Yeah, well,
you pick these things up.

545
00:36:13,964 --> 00:36:16,131
Would you care to join me?

546
00:36:20,262 --> 00:36:22,054
Can't do that.

547
00:36:22,639 --> 00:36:24,515
That would be cheating.
Oh.

548
00:36:26,434 --> 00:36:28,519
Besides, I’d rather wait.

549
00:36:32,065 --> 00:36:34,650
Well, l gotta go.

550
00:36:35,110 --> 00:36:38,445
Remember, mysterious.
That's the key.

551
00:36:38,905 --> 00:36:40,239
Oh.

552
00:36:41,199 --> 00:36:46,161
Maybe order some dessert,
just to spite them.

553
00:36:46,955 --> 00:36:49,748
All right.
Make me proud.

554
00:36:59,593 --> 00:37:01,594
[LYLE LOVETT'S "SMILE" PLAYING]

555
00:37:02,804 --> 00:37:03,804
[CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKS]

556
00:37:03,972 --> 00:37:07,433
Keep the change. Thank you.
Thank you.

557
00:37:07,601 --> 00:37:09,226
Smile

558
00:37:10,353 --> 00:37:13,647
Though your heart is aching

559
00:37:14,983 --> 00:37:16,650
Smile

560
00:37:16,818 --> 00:37:20,112
Even though it's breaking

561
00:37:22,115 --> 00:37:25,159
When there are clouds

562
00:37:25,702 --> 00:37:27,870
In the sky

563
00:37:28,163 --> 00:37:30,372
You'll get by

564
00:37:31,625 --> 00:37:33,667
If you smile

565
00:37:34,419 --> 00:37:38,505
Through your fears and sorrow

566
00:37:39,549 --> 00:37:44,678
Smile and maybe tomorrow

567
00:37:47,349 --> 00:37:52,561
You'll see the sun come shining through

568
00:37:54,314 --> 00:38:01,028
If you just smile

569
00:38:01,196 --> 00:38:04,281
DOT: These are good, Birdee.
BIRDEE: Really?

570
00:38:05,825 --> 00:38:07,076
Really.

571
00:38:07,243 --> 00:38:10,913
So do you think you can find something
for me like we talked about?

572
00:38:13,416 --> 00:38:14,708
Think l can.

573
00:38:17,420 --> 00:38:18,837
Great. Thanks.

574
00:38:19,881 --> 00:38:25,302
MAN: And then you take the film, like so,
and you run it through here.

575
00:38:25,470 --> 00:38:27,972
Now, make sure that this here
is shut tight.

576
00:38:28,139 --> 00:38:32,017
Okay.
And then you just follow it along, like so.

577
00:38:32,185 --> 00:38:36,397
And then it comes out here, like so.
And then you separate it.

578
00:38:36,564 --> 00:38:39,274
Like so.
That's right.

579
00:38:39,442 --> 00:38:42,736
Now, everyone's film has to be
developed in less than an hour.

580
00:38:42,904 --> 00:38:44,571
Okay.
Otherwise it's free.

581
00:38:44,739 --> 00:38:47,574
Any questions?
Nope.

582
00:38:48,535 --> 00:38:53,038
Occasionally, we get pictures of
a somewhat questionable nature.

583
00:38:53,206 --> 00:38:55,958
Naked pictures?
Oh, we never comment on them.

584
00:38:56,126 --> 00:38:59,545
We just hand them over
as if we hadn't seen a thing.

585
00:38:59,713 --> 00:39:01,005
I understand, Mr. Davis.

586
00:39:01,172 --> 00:39:02,965
But first, we make a copy.

587
00:39:03,133 --> 00:39:05,759
And we put them in the second drawer
under the counter.

588
00:39:05,927 --> 00:39:07,928
And you can have a look
any time you want.

589
00:39:08,096 --> 00:39:10,180
Just don't take any of them
home with you.

590
00:39:10,348 --> 00:39:13,600
Oh, all right.
You can sit right down there.

591
00:39:13,768 --> 00:39:14,935
Okay.

592
00:39:15,103 --> 00:39:16,437
Birdee Calvert.

593
00:39:16,604 --> 00:39:17,813
[LAUGHS]

594
00:39:17,981 --> 00:39:23,444
Oh. l bet the customers
will stand in line to see you again.

595
00:39:39,753 --> 00:39:43,881
MAN: Oh, yeah, we have a full range of arts
and crafts to keep our loved ones happy.

596
00:39:44,049 --> 00:39:48,594
It's like summer camp, really,
only it's all year round. Lucky them.

597
00:39:50,055 --> 00:39:52,806
Charlie, come here.
NURSE: Here we are.

598
00:39:53,391 --> 00:39:54,892
Look who's here, Mr. C.
RAMONA: Birdee.

599
00:39:55,060 --> 00:39:58,187
NURSE: All these people just to see you.
RAMONA: Told you she was coming.

600
00:39:58,354 --> 00:39:59,646
BIRDEE:
So good to see you.

601
00:40:00,148 --> 00:40:01,899
Well, enjoy.

602
00:40:04,652 --> 00:40:07,696
So how are you keeping,
Daddy? Huh?

603
00:40:07,864 --> 00:40:09,156
What's wrong with him?

604
00:40:09,324 --> 00:40:11,408
It's just a stroke.
Nothing to worry about.

605
00:40:11,576 --> 00:40:13,619
RAMONA:
And a little Old Timer's.

606
00:40:13,787 --> 00:40:17,331
She means Alzheimer's.
RAMONA: l know what l mean.

607
00:40:17,999 --> 00:40:22,753
But you know exactly what's going on,
don't you, Daddy? Yeah.

608
00:40:22,921 --> 00:40:26,465
Oh, thank him for the bunny.
BERNICE: He doesn't even know who l am.

609
00:40:26,633 --> 00:40:28,842
BIRDEE:
Sure he does, sweetheart.

610
00:40:29,010 --> 00:40:32,679
It's just a little hard for him
to show it. Come on, say hello.

611
00:40:32,847 --> 00:40:34,807
Sure, go ahead.

612
00:40:36,017 --> 00:40:38,894
Travis, you want to kiss
your grandpa hello?

613
00:40:41,314 --> 00:40:44,024
All right. l think what we need
here is a little ice cream.

614
00:40:44,192 --> 00:40:45,526
BIRDEE:
That's a great idea.

615
00:40:45,693 --> 00:40:49,780
Let Mama and Grandpa have a little time
together. We'll be in the cafeteria, Harry.

616
00:40:49,948 --> 00:40:52,366
You'll be okay?
BIRDEE: We'll be fine.

617
00:40:53,409 --> 00:40:55,285
So.

618
00:40:58,081 --> 00:40:59,623
Well, I'll tell you one thing.

619
00:40:59,791 --> 00:41:04,378
I'm not gonna sit here and tell you
what a nice place we got you in...

620
00:41:04,546 --> 00:41:06,630
...or how good you look.

621
00:41:06,798 --> 00:41:08,132
[CHUCKLES]

622
00:41:08,424 --> 00:41:11,135
Because we're adults, right?

623
00:41:11,553 --> 00:41:13,595
Well, at least you are.

624
00:41:15,723 --> 00:41:18,892
Hey, Mama says you do that
blinking thing with your eyes.

625
00:41:19,060 --> 00:41:23,063
One blink for yes, two for no.
Can you do that?

626
00:41:23,356 --> 00:41:24,690
Hm?

627
00:41:25,692 --> 00:41:29,069
Just on your good day, huh?
I get it.

628
00:41:34,075 --> 00:41:36,451
That was Bernice, Daddy.

629
00:41:37,036 --> 00:41:38,996
You remember Bernice?

630
00:41:41,249 --> 00:41:42,416
[SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY]

631
00:41:45,378 --> 00:41:47,004
There it is.

632
00:41:50,717 --> 00:41:52,426
That's Bernice, Daddy.

633
00:41:57,640 --> 00:41:59,933
She's the best thing I ever did.

634
00:42:00,768 --> 00:42:04,479
I wish Bill could be here...

635
00:42:05,607 --> 00:42:07,399
...but we're having a bit of trouble.

636
00:42:10,945 --> 00:42:13,447
But enough of that, right?

637
00:42:14,449 --> 00:42:18,952
I'm going to write her name
right down here...

638
00:42:19,120 --> 00:42:21,580
...on the bottom of her picture.

639
00:42:22,916 --> 00:42:26,752
So when she comes back here,
maybe you could recognize her...

640
00:42:26,920 --> 00:42:30,297
...and give her a little sign or something.

641
00:42:30,465 --> 00:42:32,466
She could really use one.

642
00:42:37,805 --> 00:42:38,805
What, Daddy?

643
00:42:38,973 --> 00:42:41,141
[BOB SEGER & MARTINA McBRIDE'S
"CHANCES ARE" PLAYING]

644
00:42:43,645 --> 00:42:46,855
Chances are I’ll see you

645
00:42:47,023 --> 00:42:51,443
Somewhere in my dreams tonight

646
00:42:52,820 --> 00:42:58,659
I recall your laughter and your smile

647
00:43:02,163 --> 00:43:05,165
I remember how

648
00:43:05,333 --> 00:43:10,170
You made me feel so at ease

649
00:43:11,506 --> 00:43:17,928
I remember all your grace, your style

650
00:43:25,311 --> 00:43:28,772
Chances are I’ll hold you

651
00:43:28,940 --> 00:43:33,652
And I’ll offer all I have

652
00:43:34,988 --> 00:43:41,368
You're the only one l can't forget

653
00:43:46,416 --> 00:43:50,043
You're the best I've ever met

654
00:43:51,004 --> 00:43:53,839
BERNICE:
You don't have a daddy, either, Mom.

655
00:43:54,966 --> 00:43:57,634
BIRDEE:
Don't break that. I've had it forever.

656
00:43:58,803 --> 00:44:00,721
Come on, it's late.

657
00:44:03,975 --> 00:44:05,726
Here you go.

658
00:44:06,853 --> 00:44:10,939
My little burrito baby.
Snug as a bug in a rug.

659
00:44:11,107 --> 00:44:13,233
You're out of luck if your nose itches.

660
00:44:13,401 --> 00:44:15,736
Good night.
Night, Mom.

661
00:44:26,372 --> 00:44:29,916
Well, if it isn't Birdee Calvert.

662
00:44:30,084 --> 00:44:31,585
Bobbi-Claire Akins.

663
00:44:32,003 --> 00:44:34,421
Patterson now.
Oh, great.

664
00:44:34,589 --> 00:44:38,550
How are you? l heard
about your sad news.

665
00:44:38,718 --> 00:44:42,429
How Bill could humiliate you like that
in front of the entire world...

666
00:44:42,597 --> 00:44:44,598
...is just beyond me.

667
00:44:44,766 --> 00:44:48,602
We have a satellite dish, so we got to
see it twice. Once Central, once Mountain.

668
00:44:48,770 --> 00:44:51,480
You poor thing.
What can I do for you?

669
00:44:51,647 --> 00:44:56,610
Anyway, I brought you these.
My sister's wedding reception.

670
00:44:57,278 --> 00:45:01,365
Triple prints, please. I'll come back
after I get my hair done.

671
00:45:01,532 --> 00:45:04,034
I just love this thing
you're doing with your hair.

672
00:45:04,202 --> 00:45:08,455
It's so down-to-earth
and natural-like.

673
00:45:09,040 --> 00:45:11,792
I wish I could be more like that.

674
00:45:12,585 --> 00:45:13,794
I'm fearless that way.

675
00:45:13,961 --> 00:45:15,962
[BOTH LAUGHING]

676
00:45:22,178 --> 00:45:23,887
[MIMICKING BOBBI-CLAIRE'S LAUGH]

677
00:45:34,107 --> 00:45:37,109
BIRDEE:
No. No. No, no, no!

678
00:45:38,653 --> 00:45:39,861
No! No!

679
00:45:40,029 --> 00:45:43,740
What is the matter with you,
you big piece of crap? Ugh!

680
00:45:45,660 --> 00:45:47,077
Mr. Davis.

681
00:45:48,037 --> 00:45:50,497
I'm sorry, Bobbi-Claire.
I'm....

682
00:45:50,665 --> 00:45:55,252
Sorry? You think that does it?
These pictures were irreplaceable!

683
00:45:55,420 --> 00:45:57,879
I know, I know. Something
must have got in the gate.

684
00:45:58,089 --> 00:46:02,426
There's nothing! There's not a blur,
not a face with red eyes.

685
00:46:02,593 --> 00:46:04,469
Think Debbi-Lynn
gets married every day?

686
00:46:04,679 --> 00:46:07,013
Debbi-Lynn?
Isn't this her fourth or--?

687
00:46:07,181 --> 00:46:09,850
It is her fifth,
Miss High and Mighty.

688
00:46:10,017 --> 00:46:11,935
But they each had
very different themes.

689
00:46:12,520 --> 00:46:15,063
And now there is
nothing to show for it.

690
00:46:15,231 --> 00:46:18,608
Well, at least l caught it
before the other ones got ruined.

691
00:46:18,776 --> 00:46:21,528
Oh, yes. You are just
Little Miss Employee of the Month.

692
00:46:22,321 --> 00:46:26,074
Mr. Davis, I hope I can count on you to
make sure that this never happens again.

693
00:46:26,242 --> 00:46:29,369
And l believe you know
what I mean.

694
00:46:30,830 --> 00:46:31,872
What?

695
00:46:32,039 --> 00:46:34,040
[CHUCKLING]

696
00:46:36,002 --> 00:46:39,880
Oh, dear. Am l gonna
have to fire you?

697
00:46:40,047 --> 00:46:41,381
Oh, come on,
she'll cool off.

698
00:46:41,549 --> 00:46:44,885
It's gotta be hard carrying
around all that hair, you know?

699
00:46:46,512 --> 00:46:48,722
Well, if she sends a bill...

700
00:46:48,890 --> 00:46:52,392
...I’m gonna have to dock you,
Birdee, for at least half.

701
00:46:52,560 --> 00:46:57,147
I'm sorry.
Now, come on. Let's get this back online.

702
00:46:57,690 --> 00:47:00,400
Go get back online.
BIRDEE: Shut up.

703
00:47:03,988 --> 00:47:06,573
JUSTIN: Did you know that
you were the first girl l ever kissed?

704
00:47:06,741 --> 00:47:10,452
BIRDEE: l did know that, yup.
JUSTIN: We were playing spin the bottle.

705
00:47:10,620 --> 00:47:12,412
BIRDEE:
And you stuck your tongue in my mouth.

706
00:47:12,580 --> 00:47:14,581
I didn't know
you were supposed to do that.

707
00:47:14,749 --> 00:47:16,458
JUSTIN: Of course.
BIRDEE: l was mortified.

708
00:47:16,626 --> 00:47:18,335
I thought you were an epileptic.

709
00:47:18,503 --> 00:47:22,339
I went home and told Mama I was kissing
you and you had a seizure in my mouth.

710
00:47:23,216 --> 00:47:26,218
I was over the moon for you
back then, Birdee.

711
00:47:26,636 --> 00:47:29,554
You knew that.
No, I didn't.

712
00:47:31,641 --> 00:47:33,350
Why didn't you
ever say anything?

713
00:47:33,518 --> 00:47:35,352
Coward.
Chicken.

714
00:47:35,520 --> 00:47:37,854
Chicken, pure and simple.
Big chicken.

715
00:47:38,022 --> 00:47:39,981
I don't know.
You and Bill were up here.

716
00:47:40,149 --> 00:47:42,275
I was somewhere else.

717
00:47:42,443 --> 00:47:45,445
I mean, what would you have
said if I had asked you out?

718
00:47:47,114 --> 00:47:52,285
I don't know what l would have said.
I'm not the same person I was back then.

719
00:47:53,621 --> 00:47:55,997
How about if
I asked you out now?

720
00:47:59,544 --> 00:48:01,461
Is that what you're doing?

721
00:48:02,630 --> 00:48:04,714
Yeah,
that's what I’m doing.

722
00:48:09,053 --> 00:48:11,429
I would have to say no.

723
00:48:16,227 --> 00:48:19,187
Because I'm a married woman.
What's the matter with you?

724
00:48:19,355 --> 00:48:23,525
Not on a date, though.
Just dinner.

725
00:48:24,360 --> 00:48:28,029
Married people have to eat, right?
I don't know. l don't know.

726
00:48:28,197 --> 00:48:31,324
