01:06:40,580 --> 01:06:42,247
This is it.

972
01:07:17,534 --> 01:07:20,244
JUSTIN:
Nineteenth-century Texas pine.

973
01:07:23,498 --> 01:07:25,916
I love that smell.

974
01:07:28,670 --> 01:07:30,462
Feel this.

975
01:07:34,801 --> 01:07:35,968
It's tongue-and-groove.

976
01:07:37,887 --> 01:07:39,263
Excuse me?

977
01:07:43,059 --> 01:07:46,937
They're cut and matched
perfect to fit together.

978
01:07:48,898 --> 01:07:50,357
You, um--?

979
01:07:52,235 --> 01:07:54,445
You want to see the porch?

980
01:07:59,033 --> 01:08:00,826
JUSTIN:
It's this way.

981
01:08:04,873 --> 01:08:08,500
It's gonna have a great view,
once I get rid of that trailer.

982
01:08:11,296 --> 01:08:14,131
This is gonna wrap all the way
around the house.

983
01:08:22,974 --> 01:08:25,392
This is nice.
Yeah, they call that a swing.

984
01:08:25,560 --> 01:08:26,769
Maybe you could hang it.

985
01:08:26,936 --> 01:08:28,937
[BOTH LAUGH]

986
01:08:30,565 --> 01:08:35,235
Yeah, l could. This is from
Mom and Dad's old place.

987
01:08:35,403 --> 01:08:36,695
Yeah?
Mm-hm.

988
01:08:38,740 --> 01:08:41,658
Uh-huh. Uh-huh.

989
01:08:43,369 --> 01:08:45,496
JUSTIN: It's comfy, huh?
Yeah.

990
01:08:45,705 --> 01:08:48,832
This is gonna be a real nice house, Justin.

991
01:08:49,292 --> 01:08:52,503
Who was your architect?
You're kidding, right?

992
01:08:55,423 --> 01:08:56,882
That's half the fun.

993
01:08:57,717 --> 01:09:01,053
You go around Smithville painting
houses, and you can do this?

994
01:09:02,180 --> 01:09:05,557
Yeah.
You could do so much more.

995
01:09:07,060 --> 01:09:10,229
I guess so, huh?
You know what l meant.

996
01:09:10,396 --> 01:09:15,150
I know exactly what you meant.
You're talking about the American dream.

997
01:09:16,778 --> 01:09:21,240
You find something that you love
and then you twist it and you torture it.

998
01:09:21,991 --> 01:09:24,743
Try to find a way to make money at it.

999
01:09:24,911 --> 01:09:27,246
Spend a lifetime doing that.

1000
01:09:28,748 --> 01:09:32,751
At the end, you can't find a trace
of what you started out loving.

1001
01:09:34,420 --> 01:09:36,547
What did you start out loving?

1002
01:09:41,594 --> 01:09:42,928
I don't remember.

1003
01:09:43,096 --> 01:09:47,641
For me, it was doing things right.
That's all.

1004
01:09:47,809 --> 01:09:51,144
That's why I came back here,
so l could live the way l wanted.

1005
01:09:51,312 --> 01:09:55,274
I don't know. l figured, out of everybody,
you'd understand that.

1006
01:10:04,367 --> 01:10:05,409
I do.

1007
01:10:07,287 --> 01:10:12,583
I envy you. Everything
you love is right here.

1008
01:10:17,422 --> 01:10:19,089
Not everything, Birdee.

1009
01:10:23,136 --> 01:10:25,053
Hey, hey, hey.

1010
01:10:26,139 --> 01:10:28,098
Justin, l can't--
Shh.

1011
01:10:41,446 --> 01:10:43,447
[DEANA CARTER'S
"WHAT MAKES YOU STAY" PLAYING]

1012
01:10:47,285 --> 01:10:49,494
You are so beautiful.

1013
01:10:58,588 --> 01:11:04,009
I'm not afraid of living alone

1014
01:11:04,344 --> 01:11:09,431
l was alone before he came

1015
01:11:13,061 --> 01:11:18,899
I don't have the strength
To fight anymore

1016
01:11:19,359 --> 01:11:24,279
But this time's not the same

1017
01:11:27,075 --> 01:11:32,120
So tell me why I keep holding on

1018
01:11:34,874 --> 01:11:39,044
To something l just cannot see

1019
01:11:39,212 --> 01:11:43,757
What makes you stay

1020
01:11:43,967 --> 01:11:47,052
When your world falls apart?

1021
01:11:47,220 --> 01:11:51,098
What makes you try one more time

1022
01:11:51,265 --> 01:11:54,476
When it's not in your heart?

1023
01:11:54,852 --> 01:11:57,771
At the end of your rope

1024
01:11:57,939 --> 01:12:02,567
When you can't find any hope

1025
01:12:03,236 --> 01:12:07,906
You still look at him and say

1026
01:12:09,242 --> 01:12:12,244
"I just can't walk away"

1027
01:12:14,831 --> 01:12:21,837
Tell me, what makes you stay?

1028
01:12:33,433 --> 01:12:36,435
I'll talk to you later. Bye.

1029
01:12:48,823 --> 01:12:50,782
BIRDEE: Mama?
Kitchen!

1030
01:12:51,701 --> 01:12:54,578
BIRDEE: Where's Bernice?
RAMONA: Oh, they ate hours ago.

1031
01:12:54,746 --> 01:12:57,372
Boy, she had a face on her
like a bucket of worms.

1032
01:12:57,790 --> 01:13:00,834
And l don't know what's going on there.
What's this?

1033
01:13:01,419 --> 01:13:04,296
Oh, nothing.
I just invited Justin over for dinner.

1034
01:13:04,464 --> 01:13:08,592
He sounded like he could use cheering up.
I don't want to see Justin tonight, Mama.

1035
01:13:08,760 --> 01:13:12,429
Justin is my friend and if
he's feeling down in the dumps...

1036
01:13:12,597 --> 01:13:15,432
...and l feel like cheering him up,
that's my business.

1037
01:13:15,641 --> 01:13:20,228
This is not the time for your matchmaking.
Matchmaking? What an imagination.

1038
01:13:20,396 --> 01:13:23,482
Ugh. God.
Come on, Birdee. Come on.

1039
01:13:23,649 --> 01:13:24,983
Join us.

1040
01:13:25,151 --> 01:13:28,445
You don't have to say anything.
You know, you could just sit there.

1041
01:13:28,613 --> 01:13:33,033
Maybe, you know, you could
quietly chew or something.

1042
01:13:34,077 --> 01:13:36,536
Oh, there's nothing
you can do about it, sweetie.

1043
01:13:36,704 --> 01:13:38,622
I'm going upstairs to sleep.

1044
01:13:39,207 --> 01:13:40,665
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

1045
01:13:40,833 --> 01:13:41,917
All right.

1046
01:13:42,085 --> 01:13:44,252
Now, Birdee,
this has never been a rude house.

1047
01:13:44,420 --> 01:13:46,505
Strange, perhaps, but never rude.

1048
01:13:46,672 --> 01:13:50,342
Now, l would like you to go
and welcome our guest.

1049
01:13:50,843 --> 01:13:52,928
Hey, I'm still your mama, missy.
You move it.

1050
01:13:59,102 --> 01:14:01,019
Hello, Bernice.

1051
01:14:02,730 --> 01:14:05,107
These are for you.
Thanks, but I'm allergic.

1052
01:14:05,274 --> 01:14:08,360
Hey, Mrs. Calvert.
How are you, Justin? Glad to see you.

1053
01:14:08,528 --> 01:14:09,653
JUSTIN: How you doing?
Good.

1054
01:14:09,821 --> 01:14:11,696
BERNICE: l don't want these.
Bernice.

1055
01:14:11,864 --> 01:14:13,323
BERNICE:
But thanks anyway.

1056
01:14:13,491 --> 01:14:15,534
JUSTIN: Hey, Birdee. What's going on?
Hey, Justin.

1057
01:14:15,701 --> 01:14:19,204
JUSTIN: Oh, my goodness.
You've been cooking in here, huh?

1058
01:14:19,372 --> 01:14:21,164
RAMONA: Oh, that's nothing.
I hope you enjoy it.

1059
01:14:21,332 --> 01:14:22,374
JUSTIN:
Yes, indeed.

1060
01:14:22,542 --> 01:14:25,085
RAMONA:
Come on, let's all sit down here now.

1061
01:14:25,253 --> 01:14:27,212
That's fine.

1062
01:14:31,300 --> 01:14:32,676
You're not joining us,
Mama?

1063
01:14:32,844 --> 01:14:36,263
Oh, you know, l forgot.
I ate earlier with the children.

1064
01:14:36,430 --> 01:14:39,391
You know, I'll tell you,
this memory is really going.

1065
01:14:44,438 --> 01:14:45,772
[SIGHS]

1066
01:14:46,232 --> 01:14:47,566
[CLEARS THROAT]

1067
01:14:53,447 --> 01:14:58,118
Sorry about last night.
I'm only sorry about this morning.

1068
01:15:01,747 --> 01:15:04,833
I know you have a crush on me.
A crush?

1069
01:15:06,627 --> 01:15:10,505
Birdee, this ain't high school.
You know what l mean, Bill.

1070
01:15:12,842 --> 01:15:13,884
Justin.

1071
01:15:17,722 --> 01:15:19,931
What?
My name is Justin.

1072
01:15:20,308 --> 01:15:21,349
It ain't Bill.

1073
01:15:27,273 --> 01:15:29,774
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.
You know, Birdee...

1074
01:15:30,193 --> 01:15:32,986
...you used to be so...

1075
01:15:34,447 --> 01:15:36,114
...l don't know...

1076
01:15:37,241 --> 01:15:39,701
...audacious, bold.

1077
01:15:39,869 --> 01:15:42,287
People would stop to watch you
come down the street.

1078
01:15:42,455 --> 01:15:44,289
"Here comes that Birdee Calvert."

1079
01:15:44,457 --> 01:15:47,626
Their eyes would light up.
You could see it on their faces.

1080
01:15:47,793 --> 01:15:49,336
Look at me.

1081
01:15:50,171 --> 01:15:54,299
You think you've lost that.
I can still see it.

1082
01:15:55,384 --> 01:15:57,802
Bill can't see that.

1083
01:15:57,970 --> 01:15:59,679
You don't know anything about Bill.

1084
01:15:59,847 --> 01:16:02,974
I know that Bill could let you go.
Damn, Birdee!

1085
01:16:03,142 --> 01:16:06,645
When are you gonna face up to the fact
that he ain't coming back for you?

1086
01:16:06,812 --> 01:16:09,231
Get out of here. My daddy is coming back.
BIRDEE: Bernice.

1087
01:16:09,398 --> 01:16:11,316
BERNICE:
He loves me and he wants my mother.

1088
01:16:11,484 --> 01:16:13,777
He'll kill you if you come around here.
Stop it.

1089
01:16:13,945 --> 01:16:15,695
Tell him.
Be quiet!

1090
01:16:18,991 --> 01:16:21,284
You better go.
Yup.

1091
01:16:21,452 --> 01:16:24,996
Listen, why don't both of you go out?
Bernice and I will stay here and visit.

1092
01:16:25,164 --> 01:16:27,666
Oh, no.
That's all right.

1093
01:16:27,833 --> 01:16:31,127
When you get tired of waiting,
give me a call. l hope I’m still around.

1094
01:16:31,295 --> 01:16:33,463
Thanks, Mrs. Calvert.

1095
01:16:36,842 --> 01:16:39,678
RAMONA:
Boy, you just amaze me, Birdee.

1096
01:16:39,845 --> 01:16:42,764
You know, your love life has always
been a disaster area.

1097
01:16:42,932 --> 01:16:46,059
They ought to have those
big orange cones all around you.

1098
01:16:47,353 --> 01:16:51,064
What can I say, Mama?
I'm my own crown of thorns.

1099
01:16:51,232 --> 01:16:55,068
Hey, you think life goes on forever?

1100
01:16:55,236 --> 01:16:57,529
You think behind every chance
is another chance...

1101
01:16:57,697 --> 01:16:59,823
...and then another one and another one?

1102
01:16:59,991 --> 01:17:02,826
It's the worst kind of extravagance,
the way you spend your chances, Birdee.

1103
01:17:02,994 --> 01:17:04,536
[TRUCK ENGINE STARTS]

1104
01:17:04,704 --> 01:17:06,288
BERNICE:
Get out of here and don't come back!

1105
01:17:06,455 --> 01:17:07,497
Bernice!

1106
01:17:13,212 --> 01:17:16,589
Bernice, stop it. What is the matter
with you? What are you doing?

1107
01:17:16,757 --> 01:17:19,551
Why didn't you tell him
he loves us and is coming back?

1108
01:17:19,719 --> 01:17:21,261
Because I don't know,
all right?

1109
01:17:21,429 --> 01:17:24,556
I don't know if Daddy loves us
and l don't know if he's coming back.

1110
01:17:24,724 --> 01:17:27,267
He loves me! He loves me,
even if he doesn't love you!

1111
01:17:27,476 --> 01:17:30,562
Oh, l just sent him away.
What more do you want from me?

1112
01:17:30,730 --> 01:17:32,147
BERNICE:
I want my daddy.

1113
01:17:32,315 --> 01:17:34,274
He wouldn't have left
if you had loved him enough.

1114
01:17:34,442 --> 01:17:39,070
No, your daddy didn't love me enough.
This is all your fault and you know it.

1115
01:17:50,082 --> 01:17:51,291
TRAVIS:
Aunt Birdee.

1116
01:17:51,459 --> 01:17:56,087
Help, please, somebody.
I've fallen over and I can't get up. Help!

1117
01:17:56,422 --> 01:17:59,174
You know, that is the prettiest one.

1118
01:17:59,342 --> 01:18:03,178
[JOE ELY'S "DAM OF MY HEART"
PLAYING OVER SPEAKERS]

1119
01:18:03,346 --> 01:18:05,597
Birdee Calvert.

1120
01:18:05,765 --> 01:18:07,766
She looks like
she belongs in a bar.

1121
01:18:07,933 --> 01:18:09,351
MAN:
Why, hello, Birdee.

1122
01:18:09,518 --> 01:18:11,144
It's about time
you came by and said hi.

1123
01:18:11,312 --> 01:18:14,189
BIRDEE: Hey, Mike.
You being good?

1124
01:18:14,357 --> 01:18:15,440
Well, I’m trying to be.

1125
01:18:15,608 --> 01:18:18,860
Just doesn't seem
to be working out that way.

1126
01:18:19,945 --> 01:18:22,489
Can l get a vodka tonic,
extra lime, please?

1127
01:18:22,656 --> 01:18:24,115
You surely may.
Thanks.

1128
01:18:27,370 --> 01:18:29,412
[ON TV]
What do you want to say to Dennis?

1129
01:18:29,622 --> 01:18:33,416
You know how, late at night,
I get calls really late?

1130
01:18:34,585 --> 01:18:35,627
DENNIS:
Just say it. What?

1131
01:18:35,795 --> 01:18:37,128
RAQUEL: When they call me...
Thanks.

1132
01:18:37,296 --> 01:18:38,797
MIKE: On me.
RAQUEL:...they call me to dance.

1133
01:18:38,964 --> 01:18:40,423
Thank you.
MIKE: Hey.

1134
01:18:40,591 --> 01:18:41,800
RAQUEL:
I'm really an exotic--

1135
01:18:41,967 --> 01:18:43,259
[AUDIENCE ON TV BOOS]

1136
01:18:43,427 --> 01:18:45,762
I'm really an exotic dancer.

1137
01:18:48,224 --> 01:18:50,809
You shouldn't have done this on TV.

1138
01:18:50,976 --> 01:18:52,977
[AUDIENCE ON TV LAUGHS
AND CHEERS]

1139
01:18:58,943 --> 01:19:02,779
BIRDEE: l mean, Birdee.
I mean, what kind of name--? What--?

1140
01:19:02,947 --> 01:19:07,075
You know what happens to birdies.
They're cat food. They're target practice.

1141
01:19:07,243 --> 01:19:09,494
Birdee, Birdee, Birdee!
MIKE: Come on. Hey, come on.

1142
01:19:09,662 --> 01:19:12,997
Look, it's a good name.

1143
01:19:13,165 --> 01:19:15,208
Have some coffee.
Might wanna pace yourself.

1144
01:19:15,376 --> 01:19:18,837
Know what? I'm fine. I'm gonna go home.
You sure?

1145
01:19:19,505 --> 01:19:21,965
BOBBI-CLAIRE:
Don't let me get like that, for God sakes.

1146
01:19:22,133 --> 01:19:25,260
Don't ever let me get like that.

1147
01:19:26,095 --> 01:19:29,514
BIRDEE: l look pretty pathetic, huh? Yeah?
Uh-huh.

1148
01:19:30,015 --> 01:19:33,518
Poor woman. Husband leaves her
on national television.

1149
01:19:33,686 --> 01:19:35,854
BOBBI-CLAIRE:
I know. We cried. Ha, ha, ha.

1150
01:19:36,647 --> 01:19:39,941
You know what? Do not believe
everything you see, all right?

1151
01:19:40,109 --> 01:19:44,863
Boy, if I believed everything I saw
down at the photo shop...

1152
01:19:45,030 --> 01:19:48,491
...I’d believe Miss Bobbi-Claire
got herself some new titties.

1153
01:19:50,035 --> 01:19:52,370
[LAUGHING AND JEERING]

1154
01:19:53,372 --> 01:19:56,833
I got one word for y'all.
Polaroid!

1155
01:19:57,001 --> 01:19:58,168
Polaroid!

1156
01:19:58,335 --> 01:20:02,714
Oh, come on, Bobbi-Claire.
Don't leave.

1157
01:20:02,882 --> 01:20:06,634
Come on, you won.
Come on now, Birdee. Take it easy.

1158
01:20:06,802 --> 01:20:10,180
Oh, man.
Que sera, sera, people.

1159
01:20:12,558 --> 01:20:14,559
[BIRDEE SOBBING]

1160
01:20:16,270 --> 01:20:17,562
Birdee.

1161
01:20:17,730 --> 01:20:19,814
Are you okay?

1162
01:20:20,983 --> 01:20:24,194
BIRDEE: Whatever you do, Mama,
please, don't say anything.

1163
01:20:24,361 --> 01:20:26,321
Don't be clever, don't be smart.

1164
01:20:27,406 --> 01:20:29,824
Because I really can't take it tonight.

1165
01:20:29,992 --> 01:20:31,201
Why don't you sit on that?

1166
01:20:33,746 --> 01:20:37,123
The tiles are always so cold
in this bathroom.

1167
01:20:40,044 --> 01:20:42,795
BIRDEE:
Everything is so wrong without Bill.

1168
01:20:44,340 --> 01:20:45,590
RAMONA:
I know.

1169
01:20:45,758 --> 01:20:48,176
BIRDEE: l miss him so much.
I know.

1170
01:20:48,344 --> 01:20:50,303
BIRDEE:
He used to call me "baby."

1171
01:20:50,471 --> 01:20:53,556
I never in a million years thought
I'd be a woman who liked that...

1172
01:20:53,724 --> 01:20:56,476
...but l did, with him.

1173
01:20:56,644 --> 01:20:57,685
RAMONA:
Sure you do.

1174
01:20:59,855 --> 01:21:02,023
I miss his hands.

1175
01:21:03,067 --> 01:21:05,318
Just his hands and
the way that he would just--

1176
01:21:05,486 --> 01:21:08,488
He would put them on
the small of my back...

1177
01:21:08,656 --> 01:21:11,908
...and just lead me into a room.

1178
01:21:12,076 --> 01:21:14,619
It made me feel so safe.

1179
01:21:16,455 --> 01:21:19,415
I miss all that.
Of course you do, honey.

1180
01:21:19,583 --> 01:21:21,292
BIRDEE:
Oh, God.

1181
01:21:21,752 --> 01:21:25,463
I know it's so easy
to blame him.

1182
01:21:25,631 --> 01:21:29,634
But you know what?
I think it's me.

1183
01:21:29,802 --> 01:21:31,427
I do.

1184
01:21:32,346 --> 01:21:36,975
Because he used to look at me
and l used to see myself in his eyes.

1185
01:21:37,142 --> 01:21:39,644
And it was like he saw me.

1186
01:21:40,229 --> 01:21:42,939
And l was audacious, Mama.

1187
01:21:43,107 --> 01:21:44,732
I was.

1188
01:21:44,900 --> 01:21:49,654
And then, l don't know,
things just started to change.

1189
01:21:49,822 --> 01:21:52,991
The harder l tried to be
what he wanted me to be...

1190
01:21:53,158 --> 01:21:56,327
...the less I saw myself in his eyes.

1191
01:21:57,121 --> 01:22:00,957
Just one day,
I looked and I was gone.

1192
01:22:03,794 --> 01:22:06,588
I still see her.
No, Mom. No.

1193
01:22:06,755 --> 01:22:09,591
No. It's happening with Bernice too.

1194
01:22:09,758 --> 01:22:11,759
It's happening with Bernice.

1195
01:22:11,927 --> 01:22:15,138
She doesn't even look at me
the same way.

1196
01:22:15,306 --> 01:22:18,850
It's like there's a wall between us.

1197
01:22:19,018 --> 01:22:21,311
There's a wall and it's killing me.

1198
01:22:21,478 --> 01:22:24,939
Because the one thing that l said,
when l would grow up...

1199
01:22:25,107 --> 01:22:30,153
...if I ever had a daughter of my own,
she would know her mother loved her.

1200
01:22:30,321 --> 01:22:33,489
I would hug her
and l would tell her nice things.

1201
01:22:33,657 --> 01:22:37,285
And l wouldn't just let the daddy
do all the hugging.

1202
01:22:48,714 --> 01:22:51,257
And now I realize that--

1203
01:22:51,425 --> 01:22:54,177
I realize that it doesn't matter...

1204
01:22:54,345 --> 01:22:57,221
...who or what or when...

1205
01:22:57,389 --> 01:23:01,059
...or where the hugging happens.

1206
01:23:01,226 --> 01:23:03,061
Sometimes you just need a hug.

1207
01:23:04,438 --> 01:23:07,190
And it just didn't work out that way.

1208
01:23:07,358 --> 01:23:08,900
Well, l--

1209
01:23:12,154 --> 01:23:14,739
I've seen you hug your daughter.

1210
01:23:20,412 --> 01:23:22,580
She knows you love her.

1211
01:23:25,084 --> 01:23:29,003
Yes, mothers love their daughters...

1212
01:23:30,089 --> 01:23:33,091
...even if they show it poorly.

1213
01:24:09,545 --> 01:24:12,839
TEACHER: Hi, Julia.
Here's the talent show list.

1214
01:24:13,215 --> 01:24:15,967
It's up! The audition list is up!

1215
01:24:16,135 --> 01:24:19,345
I hope I'm near the beginning.
I'm so nervous.

1216
01:24:20,222 --> 01:24:21,723
Bernice!

1217
01:24:30,441 --> 01:24:31,482
Bernice.

1218
01:24:32,192 --> 01:24:36,571
JULIA: Hey, I was gonna do a poem.
They don't like too many poems.

1219
01:24:37,364 --> 01:24:38,948
MAN: Hey, Birdee.
Hey.

1220
01:24:39,116 --> 01:24:41,159
Chris. How are you?
Fine. What's up?

1221
01:24:41,326 --> 01:24:43,995
I was wondering if you could--
Bernice!

1222
01:24:45,372 --> 01:24:46,998
Bernice, honey!

1223
01:24:47,166 --> 01:24:49,125
Isn't that your mom?

1224
01:24:53,255 --> 01:24:55,131
BIRDEE:
Sweetheart!

1225
01:24:59,344 --> 01:25:00,344
BERNICE:
Let's go.

1226
01:25:08,353 --> 01:25:09,645
Could you give this to her?

1227
01:25:09,813 --> 01:25:11,397
She forgot her lunch.
Sure, sure.

1228
01:25:11,565 --> 01:25:15,318
Thanks. Thanks.
Good to see you again.

1229
01:25:19,490 --> 01:25:21,491
[TRISHA YEARWOOD'S
"MAKE YOU FEEL MY LOVE" PLAYING]

1230
01:25:31,460 --> 01:25:35,880
When the rain is blowing in your face

1231
01:25:36,048 --> 01:25:37,381
[THUNDER RUMBLING]

1232
01:25:37,549 --> 01:25:42,136
And the whole world is on your case

1233
01:25:43,388 --> 01:25:47,892
I could offer you a warm embrace

1234
01:25:49,061 --> 01:25:53,731
To make you feel my love

1235
01:25:54,942 --> 01:26:00,238
When evening shadows and stars appear

1236
01:26:00,948 --> 01:26:05,993
And there is no one to dry your tears

1237
01:26:07,246 --> 01:26:12,250
I could hold you for a million years

1238
01:26:12,793 --> 01:26:19,757
To make you feel my love

1239
01:26:27,641 --> 01:26:29,642
Hey, Daddy.

1240
01:26:36,191 --> 01:26:38,192
Do you remember who I am?

1241
01:26:38,360 --> 01:26:39,652
Hello.

1242
01:26:40,737 --> 01:26:41,946
Hi.

1243
01:26:44,366 --> 01:26:46,617
Isn't she beautiful?

1244
01:26:49,496 --> 01:26:51,414
Yes, sir. She sure is.

1245
01:26:52,124 --> 01:26:54,750
HARRY:
That's my daughter, Birdee.

1246
01:26:54,960 --> 01:26:56,878
She's marked for happiness.

1247
01:26:57,838 --> 01:26:59,297
And how do you know that?

1248
01:26:59,464 --> 01:27:03,634
If you look at her, child,
you'll see it.

1249
01:27:07,306 --> 01:27:09,432
My God, you're right.

1250
01:27:10,893 --> 01:27:12,518
I see it.

1251
01:27:25,824 --> 01:27:28,409
RAMONA: Hey, honey.
Your mom called a while ago.

1252
01:27:28,577 --> 01:27:30,119
She said she'd be home soon.

1253
01:27:30,287 --> 01:27:32,997
Do you want me to tuck you in?

1254
01:27:33,165 --> 01:27:35,124
Yeah? How tight?

1255
01:27:35,709 --> 01:27:38,794
Tight.
Okay.

1256
01:27:39,546 --> 01:27:43,090
Snug as a bug in a rug.

1257
01:27:43,592 --> 01:27:48,137
You're so much like your mama.
She use to love me to tuck her in real tight.

1258
01:27:49,806 --> 01:27:52,016
I'm not like her.

1259
01:27:52,267 --> 01:27:55,519
We're different.
It's like we're not even relatives.

1260
01:27:55,687 --> 01:27:58,230
Oh, well, yeah.

1261
01:27:58,440 --> 01:28:01,651
Yeah, l know what you mean.

1262
01:28:02,069 --> 01:28:05,071
Relatives are trouble.
I couldn't agree more.

1263
01:28:05,989 --> 01:28:10,534
I ever tell you about Walter,
my brother? No?

1264
01:28:11,328 --> 01:28:13,704
Well, what you have to go through
with your mama...

1265
01:28:13,872 --> 01:28:16,958
...the suffering,
that's what l had to suffer with Walter.

1266
01:28:17,584 --> 01:28:20,670
One day, we were playing out back,
down by the river...

1267
01:28:20,879 --> 01:28:26,467
...and we came across
the most beautiful anthill you ever saw.

1268
01:28:26,635 --> 01:28:30,721
And then Walter, he immediately kicked it
and stomped on it...

1269
01:28:30,889 --> 01:28:33,766
...and just scattered it
to the four winds.

1270
01:28:33,976 --> 01:28:36,727
I just started howling. I was just--

1271
01:28:36,895 --> 01:28:39,355
I yelled for my mama.
I ran up and I grabbed her...

1272
01:28:39,523 --> 01:28:42,733
...and dragged her down there,
just crying and carrying on.

1273
01:28:43,193 --> 01:28:47,029
Anyway, my mama was trying to
calm me down, so she said:

1274
01:28:47,197 --> 01:28:51,492
"Wait, wait. They're not finished.
Not by a long shot."

1275
01:28:51,660 --> 01:28:55,371
And we waited and waited
and sure enough...

1276
01:28:55,539 --> 01:29:00,876
...those little black specks just started
scurrying every which way...

1277
01:29:01,044 --> 01:29:04,839
...just working hard to build
their home back.

1278
01:29:05,007 --> 01:29:09,802
And l said, "Why did they do it?
I'd just give up. I mean, it's hopeless."

1279
01:29:10,721 --> 01:29:15,141
And my mama said, "Yeah, you know,
if there's just one of you.

1280
01:29:15,308 --> 01:29:17,476
But there's lots of ants down there.

1281
01:29:17,644 --> 01:29:22,440
And they're all relatives.
They're family, just like we are."

1282
01:29:23,400 --> 01:29:28,362
Well, that's what families are for.
That's why they invented families.

1283
01:29:28,780 --> 01:29:32,033
So hopeless didn't get the last word.

1284
01:29:32,200 --> 01:29:35,703
So listen, if ants can do it,
I figure we can do it.

1285
01:29:35,912 --> 01:29:37,913
[BOTH CHUCKLE]

1286
01:29:40,208 --> 01:29:44,920
You know, my Birdee has a lot more
strength than she's ever known.

1287
01:29:46,089 --> 01:29:50,134
And one of these days,
she's going to realize it.

1288
01:29:55,223 --> 01:30:00,478
I love you, Grandma.
Oh, honey. Honey.

1289
01:30:02,522 --> 01:30:04,106
"My cup runneth over."

1290
01:30:12,908 --> 01:30:17,161
Say, haven't you got a birthday
coming up here pretty soon?

1291
01:30:17,329 --> 01:30:20,831
You want to tell Grandma
what you wish for? No?

1292
01:30:20,999 --> 01:30:22,666
No.
No?

1293
01:30:22,834 --> 01:30:26,670
Well, never mind. I'll figure that out.

1294
01:30:26,838 --> 01:30:30,132
I have my magic ways.

1295
01:30:31,760 --> 01:30:34,512
Good night, honey.
Good night.

1296
01:30:45,107 --> 01:30:47,316
Oh, Birdee.

1297
01:30:47,609 --> 01:30:51,529
When did you get home?
Oh, a little while ago.

1298
01:30:51,696 --> 01:30:54,031
I went to go see Daddy.

1299
01:30:54,199 --> 01:30:56,325
Oh, that's nice.
Yeah.

1300
01:30:56,952 --> 01:30:58,619
Well, you were always
Daddy's girl.

1301
01:31:01,581 --> 01:31:04,375
Not just his, Mama.

1302
01:31:05,919 --> 01:31:07,545
Thank you.

1303
01:31:11,174 --> 01:31:12,550
Well...

1304
01:31:13,760 --> 01:31:15,845
...you're most welcome.

1305
01:31:19,516 --> 01:31:23,894
I'm gonna get some tea. You want some?
No, I'm okay. Thanks.

1306
01:31:46,251 --> 01:31:48,252
[GRUNTING]

1307
01:32:05,061 --> 01:32:07,980
BERNICE: Grandma? Grandma?
Mama?

1308
01:32:10,025 --> 01:32:13,611
BERNICE: Grandma!
Mama? Mama?

1309
01:32:13,778 --> 01:32:17,406
Mama, what's up? Mama,
what's wrong? Mama? Mama?

1310
01:32:17,574 --> 01:32:20,576
Oh, God! Mama--
Bernice, go dial 91 1 .

1311
01:32:20,744 --> 01:32:22,578
Mama. This isn't happening to me.

1312
01:32:22,787 --> 01:32:25,706
Come on, not now, Mama. Not now.
Don't do this to me now, Mama.

1313
01:32:25,874 --> 01:32:28,626
Come on, Mama, don't do this to me now.
Wake up, Mama.

1314
01:32:28,793 --> 01:32:31,879
Mama, wake up! Wake up! Mama!

1315
01:32:32,047 --> 01:32:36,634
Mama, please.
Oh, God. Oh, God. Oh, God.

1316
01:32:36,801 --> 01:32:39,637
No. No. No.

1317
01:33:44,286 --> 01:33:46,287
[SOBBING]

1318
01:34:13,231 --> 01:34:16,984
PRIEST: I’m privileged to have known
Ramona Calvert all my life.

1319
01:34:17,152 --> 01:34:22,906
I don't believe she needs to be idealized
in death beyond what she was in life.

1320
01:34:23,533 --> 01:34:27,161
A complicated woman
and a generous one.

1321
01:34:27,370 --> 01:34:31,206
Proud, and yet humble enough
to help many of her neighbors...

1322
01:34:31,374 --> 01:34:33,250
...quietly, simply.

1323
01:34:34,419 --> 01:34:38,756
The mother of two fine daughters.
The wife of one good man.

1324
01:34:39,382 --> 01:34:44,094
She doesn't require any fancy words
from the likes of me.

1325
01:34:44,262 --> 01:34:48,932
All I need to say is I will miss her,
as will we all.

1326
01:34:49,100 --> 01:34:52,770
And l know,
even seated next to our Father....

1327
01:34:52,937 --> 01:34:55,564
Daddy, he's back.
He came back for us.

1328
01:34:55,732 --> 01:34:57,649
He came back.
Thank you, Grandma.

1329
01:34:57,817 --> 01:35:00,486
Thank you.
May she rest in peace.

1330
01:35:00,653 --> 01:35:04,239
In the name of the Father,
the Son and the Holy Spirit.

1331
01:35:04,407 --> 01:35:05,449
Amen.

1332
01:35:05,617 --> 01:35:08,702
PRIEST: May God be with you.
And also with you.

1333
01:35:16,169 --> 01:35:19,171
Daddy, l knew you'd come back!
I knew it!

1334
01:35:19,381 --> 01:35:23,425
Take it easy, Bernice. You're choking me.
Come on. Let me get a look at you.

1335
01:35:28,598 --> 01:35:30,891
What are you doing?
Taking it home.

1336
01:35:31,101 --> 01:35:32,684
Okay.

1337
01:35:33,353 --> 01:35:35,020
Hey.
You doing all right?

1338
01:35:35,188 --> 01:35:38,607
Yeah. Thanks.

1339
01:35:40,860 --> 01:35:42,653
BERNICE:
Want to come see Mama?

1340
01:36:07,095 --> 01:36:08,137
Hey, Travis.

1341
01:36:11,766 --> 01:36:13,350
You mind if l sit down?

1342
01:36:27,866 --> 01:36:31,034
Birdee, why don't you sit down?
That can wait.

1343
01:36:34,414 --> 01:36:36,999
BIRDEE: Would you like sugar or cream
with that or are you okay?

1344
01:36:37,167 --> 01:36:38,625
No, I'm fine.

1345
01:36:40,545 --> 01:36:42,087
BIRDEE:
How are you? You want anything?

1346
01:36:42,255 --> 01:36:44,882
BERNICE: I’m good.
Yeah? Okay.

1347
01:36:49,179 --> 01:36:50,971
You got a telegram?

1348
01:36:54,601 --> 01:36:57,019
I waited my whole life
to get one of these.

1349
01:36:57,979 --> 01:36:59,646
Still ain't happened.

1350
01:37:04,110 --> 01:37:05,736
It's from your mom?

1351
01:37:09,199 --> 01:37:12,576
I tell you, she must care about you
an awful lot to send you a telegram.

1352
01:37:14,579 --> 01:37:16,830
It's for Aunt Birdee.

1353
01:37:20,001 --> 01:37:21,502
Even so.

1354
01:37:24,631 --> 01:37:26,757
What you thinking about?

1355
01:37:28,218 --> 01:37:30,469
Whether Aunt Birdee wants me.

1356
01:37:33,765 --> 01:37:35,724
Yeah, she does.

1357
01:37:39,687 --> 01:37:42,064
My grandma's dead.

1358
01:37:48,780 --> 01:37:50,280
I know.

1359
01:37:52,700 --> 01:37:55,786
BILL: Birdee, you're not gonna
make me feel bad about this.

1360
01:37:56,162 --> 01:37:58,247
Only thing I’m guilty of
is falling in love.

1361
01:37:58,665 --> 01:38:02,793
I didn't want it to happen.
I didn't seek it out, Birdee. It just happened.

1362
01:38:02,961 --> 01:38:05,462
Oh, I’m sorry.
Are you talking about me or Connie?

1363
01:38:05,630 --> 01:38:10,467
Because you seem to fall in love real easily,
so it's only natural to be confused.

1364
01:38:11,803 --> 01:38:15,514
BERNICE: Here you go, Daddy.
Didn't l tell you to play outside?

1365
01:38:15,682 --> 01:38:19,851
I'm not leaving until you stop fighting.
We're not fighting. Nobody's fighting here.

1366
01:38:20,019 --> 01:38:22,980
Nope, you never did,
did you?

1367
01:38:23,147 --> 01:38:26,817
Things always came real easy to you,
didn't they? Real easy.

1368
01:38:26,985 --> 01:38:30,946
Hey, almost as easy as discarding
your wife and child, huh?

1369
01:38:31,114 --> 01:38:33,448
Kind of like a to-do list.

1370
01:38:33,616 --> 01:38:37,494
Wife's gone, check.
Daughter's gone, check, check.

1371
01:38:37,662 --> 01:38:39,580
Birdee, you left, remember?

1372
01:38:39,747 --> 01:38:43,250
No, you left long before l left you.

1373
01:38:43,668 --> 01:38:45,877
This isn't about who left first, Birdee.

1374
01:38:47,005 --> 01:38:49,590
We're not in love
with each other anymore.

1375
01:38:49,757 --> 01:38:51,842
BERNICE:
You said you weren't gonna fight.

1376
01:38:52,010 --> 01:38:56,013
Bernice, if you do not get out of this house,
you're gonna wish you had.

1377
01:38:56,180 --> 01:38:58,140
Don't you ruin anything.

1378
01:38:59,767 --> 01:39:03,604
Look, if you fell out of love with me,
you should have left a long time ago...

1379
01:39:03,771 --> 01:39:05,897
...instead of skirting around
behind my back.

1380
01:39:08,192 --> 01:39:10,527
Maybe I'll go there one day.

1381
01:39:12,614 --> 01:39:14,448
Where's that?

1382
01:39:14,616 --> 01:39:16,533
California.

1383
01:39:16,951 --> 01:39:18,785
To see my mom.

1384
01:39:21,456 --> 01:39:23,874
Yeah, I’m sure
she'd like that a lot.

1385
01:39:24,834 --> 01:39:26,376
Yeah.

1386
01:39:30,298 --> 01:39:33,300
How come you're sitting
out here all by yourself?

1387
01:39:34,719 --> 01:39:37,012
Where's that crazy Bernice?

1388
01:39:37,430 --> 01:39:39,765
She's inside with her father.

1389
01:39:42,393 --> 01:39:43,560
Everything's okay, right?

1390
01:39:44,896 --> 01:39:46,229
Yeah.

1391
01:39:46,898 --> 01:39:50,734
What do you feel like doing?
Want to go for a walk or something?

1392
01:39:51,611 --> 01:39:54,071
Aren't you going inside to say hi?

1393
01:39:56,074 --> 01:39:57,741
Don't you know?

1394
01:39:59,160 --> 01:40:02,245
I came over to say hi to you.
Hi.

1395
01:40:02,914 --> 01:40:06,750
God, I would have stayed
with you forever.

1396
01:40:07,835 --> 01:40:11,630
I would have turned myself
inside out for you.

1397
01:40:11,798 --> 01:40:14,341
Birdee, I wouldn't have let you.

1398
01:40:15,593 --> 01:40:20,764
People grow. They change. They have to.
You don't think l know that?

1399
01:40:23,267 --> 01:40:27,437
I know that I'm not what l once was.

1400
01:40:27,605 --> 01:40:29,523
I know that.

1401
01:40:30,191 --> 01:40:31,942
But then again, neither are you.

1402
01:40:32,694 --> 01:40:36,697
You're sad, you're weak, and you're...

1403
01:40:36,906 --> 01:40:40,117
...shorter, if you want to know the truth.

1404
01:40:40,410 --> 01:40:45,247
But l haven't changed so much that
I would go and lie to somebody that l loved.

1405
01:40:45,790 --> 01:40:52,254
God, I would walk through fire before
I let them feel like they were nothing.

1406
01:40:53,089 --> 01:40:57,008
And l would never break up
anybody's home.

1407
01:40:57,176 --> 01:41:01,304
Because I'm not a quitter.
I care about my family.

1408
01:41:02,014 --> 01:41:03,849
I'm in love with Connie.

1409
01:41:05,768 --> 01:41:09,521
Birdee, this is my chance for a fresh start
and I’m taking it. I'm sorry.

1410
01:41:09,689 --> 01:41:11,773
Then you should take it.

1411
01:41:13,401 --> 01:41:15,652
If that's your chance,
then you should take it.

1412
01:41:16,446 --> 01:41:19,698
You're right.
You and Connie deserve each other.

1413
01:41:19,866 --> 01:41:22,117
You were lucky to have me.

1414
01:41:22,285 --> 01:41:24,119
But you know what?

1415
01:41:24,287 --> 01:41:28,331
I think I already got the best part of you.

1416
01:41:31,002 --> 01:41:33,003
And she's standing right out there.

1417
01:41:33,171 --> 01:41:35,714
And she's waiting for me.

1418
01:41:35,882 --> 01:41:41,511
I don't know. What's left over just all of
a sudden doesn't look so good anymore.

1419
01:41:42,305 --> 01:41:45,015
So, what do you want?
Why did you come back?

1420
01:41:45,183 --> 01:41:47,851
You want my permission?

1421
01:41:49,145 --> 01:41:53,523
You want my condolences?
Why did you come back?

1422
01:41:55,651 --> 01:41:59,696
I didn't want to do this today,
but it's because I want a divorce, Birdee.

1423
01:42:02,867 --> 01:42:05,118
BERNICE:
I'm coming with you, Daddy!

1424
01:42:32,355 --> 01:42:35,649
BIRDEE: Bernice.
I'm going with my daddy.

1425
01:42:40,488 --> 01:42:42,906
BILL:
Bernice, what do you think you're doing?

1426
01:42:43,074 --> 01:42:44,991
I'm going with you.

1427
01:42:45,159 --> 01:42:47,244
BILL:
Honey, that's impossible.

1428
01:42:47,411 --> 01:42:48,578
But I’m going with you.

1429
01:42:48,746 --> 01:42:51,414
BILL: No. You gotta stay here
with your mama.

1430
01:42:51,582 --> 01:42:54,000
Birdee, you gonna help me out here?

1431
01:42:54,335 --> 01:42:57,128
You told me you wanted me
with you, remember?

1432
01:42:57,296 --> 01:43:00,006
Listen, honey. I’ve gotta go.

1433
01:43:00,842 --> 01:43:05,011
Now, don't do this to yourself, okay?
Don't make a scene.

1434
01:43:05,179 --> 01:43:07,389
Now, go on back inside.
Go ahead.

1435
01:43:19,819 --> 01:43:21,778
Stop it, Daddy!

1436
01:43:22,154 --> 01:43:23,780
Bernice.

1437
01:43:24,156 --> 01:43:26,950
You know I'd take you with me if I could.
You can!

